HEADWORD: Clearedness
<hw>Clear"ed*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality of
being cleared.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Imputed by his friends to the <qex>clearedness</qex>, by his foes
to the searedness, of his conscience.</q> <rj><qau>T.
Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

